medium: Bound portfolio of fifteen gelatin silver prints
inscribed:
Cover printed recto upper center: These Images
Cover printed recto lower center: MINOR WHITE
Cover printed verso center: Searching for the wake of your ship / images of ocean interfere / So like you have these images become / they have usurped reality

Back cover printed recto center: From the first printing ofthe negatives / six unnumbered sets resulted with the title/ Song Without Words 1947. / For the second printing in 1950 a shorter / sequence was invented, titled These Images. / This is set no. 6 [inscribed in graphite] of 24. / Minor White [signed in graphite] / Printed by Adrian Wilson at the Sign of the Interplayers.
